---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Eyebrow from '../components/Eyebrow.astro';

const lastUpdated = '27 April 2026';
---
<Layout
  title="Privacy & cookies — AWJ"
  description="How AWJ handles your data, cookies, and analytics. Plain English, no nonsense."
>
  <section class="pv">
    <div class="content-shell pv__inner">
      <Eyebrow>Privacy</Eyebrow>
      <h1 class="pv__title awj-display">Privacy & cookies.</h1>
      <p class="pv__lede">
        Plain English. The short version: AWJ collects the minimum needed to know
        which essays land. No ads, no data sold to anyone, no creepy stuff.
      </p>
      <p class="pv__updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <div class="pv__body prose">
        <h2>What I collect</h2>
        <p>Two analytics tools run on this site:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> — privacy-first, cookieless.
            Counts pageviews and referrers in aggregate. No cookies, no fingerprinting,
            no personal data leaves your browser.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> — only if you click Accept on the cookie
            banner. Used to understand which essays are read, how far through, and
            which subscribe forms convert. Your IP is anonymised before storage.
            If you click Decline (or ignore the banner), GA runs in cookieless mode —
            no cookies set, only aggregate signals retained.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Newsletter (Beehiiv)</h2>
        <p>
          When you subscribe to the journal, your email is sent to
          <a href="https://www.beehiiv.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Beehiiv</a>,
          which delivers the weekly entry. You can unsubscribe with one click from
          any email. Beehiiv handles the data per their own
          <a href="https://www.beehiiv.com/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">privacy policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact form</h2>
        <p>
          Messages sent via the contact form go to my inbox via
          <a href="https://resend.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Resend</a>.
          I'll only use what you send me to reply.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies in detail</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Strictly necessary:</strong> none beyond the consent choice itself
            (stored in browser localStorage, not a cookie).</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics (only after Accept):</strong> Google Analytics sets
            <code>_ga</code>, <code>_ga_*</code>. Used for visit attribution and
            returning-user identification. Retention: 14 months.</li>
          <li><strong>Marketing / ads:</strong> none. AWJ doesn't run ads.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Your choices</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Click <strong>Decline</strong> on the cookie banner — no cookies set.</li>
          <li>Use Google's
            <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="noopener" target="_blank">opt-out browser add-on</a>
            for site-wide opt-out across the web.</li>
          <li>Email <a href="mailto:hello@andywhyte.com">hello@andywhyte.com</a> to
            request access, correction, or deletion of any personal data I hold
            (mainly your subscriber email, if applicable).</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>UK GDPR + PECR</h2>
        <p>
          AWJ is operated from the United Kingdom. The lawful basis for processing
          subscriber emails is your consent (you opted in). The lawful basis for
          analytics with your consent is also consent; in cookieless mode, it's
          legitimate interest (aggregate site improvement, no personal data stored).
          You can withdraw consent at any time by clicking Decline or clearing
          your browser's localStorage for andywhyte.com.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Andy Whyte — <a href="mailto:hello@andywhyte.com">hello@andywhyte.com</a>.
          For any data-protection question, that's the address.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .pv { padding: var(--sp-9) 0 var(--sp-9); }
  .pv__inner { padding: 0 var(--gutter); }
  .pv__title { margin: var(--sp-3) 0; font-size: clamp(48px, 8vw, 128px); line-height: 0.9; }
  .pv__lede {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: clamp(18px, 1.6vw, 22px);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--fg-2);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin: 0 0 var(--sp-3);
  }
  .pv__updated {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--fg-3);
    margin: 0 0 var(--sp-7);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .pv__body { max-width: 70ch; }
  .pv__body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 400;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-size: clamp(28px, 3vw, 40px);
    margin: var(--sp-7) 0 var(--sp-3);
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  }
  .pv__body p, .pv__body li {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--fg-1);
  }
  .pv__body ul { padding-left: 1.2em; }
  .pv__body li { margin: 0.4em 0; }
  .pv__body a { color: var(--awj-blue); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .pv__body a:hover { color: var(--awj-black); }
  .pv__body code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--awj-grey-100);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
</style>
